<body>
    <h1>20260618 - Lapu-Lapu GOCC</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p local-id=3D"8d5b5639b938">Generated by AI. Be sure to check for =
accuracy.</p>
<p local-id=3D"d9f1573e56e9">Meeting notes:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"b7362ce8-f6a8-476f-951a-af848929413a">
<li local-id=3D"836ffde8-c338-4903-be5f-739c4df48c6c">
<p local-id=3D"dcdbba5232f0"><strong>Employee and Developer Experience Dash=
boards: </strong>David updated the team, including Rae and Jonan, on progre=
ss with the employee experience and business capability dashboards, discuss=
ed feedback from the sales team, and outlined ongoing efforts to integrate =
external monitoring data and refine the developer experience dashboard, par=
ticularly addressing recurring issues with the Solace application.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"050801aa-1d27-4ef0-bfb7-d7c2f56e9571">
<li local-id=3D"6e7590d6-ca95-4139-8f06-4d5f6334c962">
<p local-id=3D"697d6dee532f"><strong>Sales Team Feedback: </strong>David re=
ported that a member of the sales team and other key business stakeholders =
found the employee experience and business capability dashboards very usefu=
l for monitoring branch office and application status, and requested furthe=
r access and feedback mechanisms.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"89267b68-9165-4245-b824-1278e3f4532b">
<p local-id=3D"27ae673f2d86"><strong>Integration with New Relic and Power B=
I: </strong>David and Rae are exploring the possibility of importing extern=
al reports from New Relic into Power BI to enhance dashboard functionality,=
 while also working to provide direct access to New Relic for relevant busi=
ness users.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4cee2df9-92eb-4537-8730-efb3616891f1">
<p local-id=3D"55a3b4abe0d8"><strong>Developer Experience Dashboard Refinem=
ent: </strong>David described ongoing refinement of the developer experienc=
e dashboard, focusing on the Solace application, which exhibits unstable en=
vironments; he has contacted the app owner and is collaborating with the te=
st environment team to investigate and address the recurring system errors.=
</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ebd97da5-d4b8-4cff-8580-81440821af08">
<p local-id=3D"b9e29ca70900"><strong>Alert Process Improvement: </strong>Jo=
nan emphasized the need to reinforce processes for recurring alerts, ensuri=
ng that such issues are promptly identified and addressed, and discussed co=
ordination with Mark and the test environment management team to improve mo=
nitoring and escalation procedures.</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"d00b9b50-8375-4c31-88ea-a11e5febd188">
<p local-id=3D"7d2c88bfd8b1"><strong>Automated Monitoring and Incident Resp=
onse Enhancements: </strong>Jonan, Mary, and Mark discussed plans to automa=
te monitoring and incident response for non-production environments, includ=
ing integration with Moogsoft and Ansible, and outlined interim manual proc=
esses and timelines for implementation.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"a7c23777-cdaa-412a-b14d-759ef0cd6a8b">
<li local-id=3D"25b2e7ce-3d1f-43dd-976b-4b0252f02ddc">
<p local-id=3D"41e734de4205"><strong>Moogsoft and Ansible Integration Plan:=
 </strong>Jonan explained that the team plans to integrate monitoring alert=
s with Moogsoft, triggering an Ansible script to automatically restart serv=
ices upon failure; if the automated restart fails, incidents will escalate =
to GOCC and, if necessary, to L2 support.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e57cf22a-2168-4b5c-8ed3-18bb6c714511">
<p local-id=3D"cf5117ba6bc2"><strong>Implementation Timeline: </strong>Mary=
 provided an estimated timeline, stating that Moogsoft integration is expec=
ted by the end of the month or early next month, while Ansible integration =
will require additional testing and will be implemented after initial Moogs=
oft deployment.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8af99f68-2592-4044-8fdc-8a53cab96050">
<p local-id=3D"8c43a933f615"><strong>Manual Interim Process: </strong>Until=
 full automation is achieved, the team will manually run the Ansible script=
 in response to incidents, with Moogsoft registering incidents after valida=
tion and requiring human intervention for service restarts.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3ebdc324-3278-46a3-8f1c-803afd6deb28">
<p local-id=3D"a3c83962fc39"><strong>Root Cause Analysis and Alert Routing:=
 </strong>Jonan noted that the current L2 team is investigating the root ca=
uses of repeated failures, and MK is working with the observability team to=
 ensure alerts are properly routed to GOCC, addressing previous issues with=
 reactive incident handling.</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"3462be87-1c87-41dc-855b-be3c2c471c7b">
<p local-id=3D"edf67fcc0991"><strong>Firewall Approvals and Application URL=
 Monitoring: </strong>Balaji, Rae, Mark, and Jonan discussed the status of =
firewall approvals required for Enginium application URL monitoring in non-=
production environments, clarified the approval process, and addressed issu=
es with outdated URLs and validation procedures.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"04ffa27b-9a93-4c69-a973-e137f8da7054">
<li local-id=3D"863ad403-d167-4096-b154-1abb41e29891">
<p local-id=3D"1e235924762d"><strong>Pending Firewall Requests: </strong>Ra=
e reported that a firewall request for Enginium is pending approval, with c=
oordination ongoing with the observability team and Paula, and Mark clarifi=
ed that the request involves switching to Azure jump due to decommissioning=
 of the on-premise server.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"21392a5c-c4c7-4230-a673-2a881a137da0">
<p local-id=3D"13e800c0ef42"><strong>Validation and Monitoring Impact: </st=
rong>Balaji highlighted that incomplete firewall approvals previously preve=
nted GOCC from completing application validation during non-production patc=
hing, and expressed hope that completion would enable validation for upcomi=
ng production patching.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"bab43452-3224-41ad-a160-3d7847664ba7">
<p local-id=3D"788995ad203c"><strong>URL Accuracy and Updates: </strong>Dav=
id pointed out that some Enginium environments listed in the monitoring she=
et are outdated or incorrectly reference old environments, and Rae confirme=
d that updated URLs have been provided and recorded in the worksheet.</p></=
li>
<li local-id=3D"93f69f8a-6ffc-441a-81ac-176e9fdef47b">
<p local-id=3D"6f500e4ac231"><strong>Action Items for Approvals: </strong>J=
onan instructed Mark and Rae to closely monitor the firewall approval proce=
ss to ensure timely completion and avoid further delays in application moni=
toring and validation.</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"0245cb03-3923-407e-a7a0-9a23901c55f7">
<p local-id=3D"891fd1e72d0a"><strong>L1/L2/L3 Support Roles and Runbook Cla=
rification: </strong>Balaji, Jonan, Birger, and Dennis discussed the curren=
t and future structure of L1, L2, and L3 support roles for Ingenium, clarif=
ied escalation procedures, and agreed to maintain the current runbook until=
 the GOCC operating model transitions in September.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"ed693394-f256-4a0a-979a-91d7f19f2627">
<li local-id=3D"307cfcf6-c866-4f6d-98aa-84934924c8d5">
<p local-id=3D"8918fae883b9"><strong>Current Escalation Procedures: </stron=
g>Balaji raised questions about the absence of L2 roles in the Ingenium run=
book and sought clarification on escalation paths, particularly for scenari=
os requiring immediate action or further investigation beyond L1 capabiliti=
es.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4cf210dc-fe74-468d-b2b0-6954e37c5e7f">
<p local-id=3D"8f6d50504744"><strong>Future GOCC Operating Model: </strong>=
Jonan explained that by September, the GOCC will transition to a unified op=
erational team without L1/L2 silos, with a single engineer handling all sup=
port tasks, and confirmed that the current structure and resources will rem=
ain unchanged until then.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9f9a5806-d5cc-4951-b9b2-7846cf9553f1">
<p local-id=3D"49c7e821575f"><strong>Runbook Updates and Agreement: </stron=
g>Balaji and Jonan agreed to retain the existing runbook for Japan market a=
pplications until the new GOCC model is implemented, after which the runboo=
k will be updated to reflect the revised support structure.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e02877f5-b73c-408e-9bc0-5947c27400e8">
<p local-id=3D"9192d46d82d9"><strong>Support Role Clarification: </strong>B=
irger and Jonan clarified the procedural flow from automation (L0) through =
L1 and L2, specifying that specialized troubleshooting not covered by proce=
dures should escalate to L2, and only unresolved or complex issues should r=
each L3.</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"e8e5340f-ddd1-47e6-9ad7-e86baeb1f5f7">
<p local-id=3D"3d73f9db99b6"><strong>GOCC Transition and Runbook Standardiz=
ation: </strong>David, Jonan, Birger, and Rae discussed the ongoing transit=
ion of applications to GOCC, the need for standardized and up-to-date runbo=
oks, and challenges related to scope, sign-off, and automation of health ch=
ecks and escalation procedures.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"4f045cce-2859-4e65-b30f-78a74d8e3e74">
<li local-id=3D"3466cd3d-9a97-4ad4-a69e-401d3c4bc447">
<p local-id=3D"a2ba9f7293a7"><strong>Runbook Format and Maintenance: </stro=
ng>David and Birger discussed the drawbacks of outdated or manually maintai=
ned runbooks, suggesting improvements such as metadata extraction, version =
control, and integration with ServiceNow to ensure accuracy and facilitate =
automation.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"96f887b5-04a4-47b4-8c80-2375c91004b9">
<p local-id=3D"76ac42f32184"><strong>Scope and Sign-Off Clarification: </st=
rong>Rae and Angelo clarified that several remaining applications are curre=
ntly out of scope for GOCC transition, with Rae tasked to follow up with Do=
nna and the AMS team to determine the reasons and report back to David and =
Jonan.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c8f5f004-27d1-479d-ad07-3f2e57d9a82f">
<p local-id=3D"900fbd05e48b"><strong>Levels of Monitoring Responsibility: <=
/strong>Birger and Jonan distinguished between basic availability monitorin=
g (e.g., up/down status) and more granular performance or capacity monitori=
ng, agreeing that at minimum, availability monitoring should remain in scop=
e even if other aspects are excluded.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6713e8f4-ebdf-472e-850f-eea02e148539">
<p local-id=3D"215658a80ea4"><strong>Escalation and Communication Procedure=
s: </strong>The team discussed the use of XMatters for automated escalation=
 and communication in case of incidents, emphasizing the importance of havi=
ng clear routing and escalation paths documented and tested as part of the =
transition process.</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"d418b78d-93d8-4b64-bb45-c07d7f8747f8">
<p local-id=3D"1ad1db6d3686"><strong>Rapid Recovery Plan and Knowledge Base=
 Publication: </strong>David, Jonan, Birger, and Mary reviewed the status o=
f the rapid recovery plan and MMM level 2 for Ingenium, confirmed the publi=
cation of the relevant knowledge base article, and discussed next steps for=
 extending the plan to other applications and departments.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"780c0a4f-cff5-41e8-8883-1b4773ea2a46">
<li local-id=3D"d4e12cd4-47d9-4def-8fde-241df8063f5e">
<p local-id=3D"a30c0cee5ed8"><strong>Ingenium Rapid Recovery Completion: </=
strong>David confirmed that the rapid recovery plan for Ingenium is complet=
e and the knowledge base article has been published, with Jonan and Birger =
agreeing to review and suggest edits as needed.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9ef5a066-4b12-4c91-b306-595a7453069c">
<p local-id=3D"7f6a4a3a6216"><strong>Extension to Other Applications: </str=
ong>David noted that while Ingenium is complete, extending the rapid recove=
ry plan to other applications requires coordination with the PS team and ad=
ditional approvals, with Harish and Hirooka San involved in facilitating th=
is process.</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"a8176343-30ed-4f05-a3bf-4d67e83e5553">
<p local-id=3D"9c98abc46c86"><strong>Branch Office Monitoring Expansion: </=
strong>David, Jonan, and Birger discussed the deployment of monitoring solu=
tions in the Philippines branch office, addressed customization for local s=
ites, and considered potential collaboration with other regions such as Sin=
gapore.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"aed6b3d5-ce4a-4a9a-8781-b0020e7bb038">
<li local-id=3D"44567a56-3649-4575-932e-bd1d7f43d5c3">
<p local-id=3D"2ccec4dbf7fc"><strong>Philippines Branch Monitoring Setup: <=
/strong>David announced that monitoring is now operational in the Philippin=
es branch office, with Jonan and Birger confirming the site details and dis=
cussing the replacement of Japan-specific monitoring items with local custo=
mer sites.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"309832c6-b855-4b90-acf2-5e7cfdc1ec94">
<p local-id=3D"eb97de2e1074"><strong>Regional Collaboration Opportunities: =
</strong>Birger mentioned that Singapore has expressed interest in similar =
monitoring solutions, suggesting future collaboration and knowledge sharing=
 across regions.</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"cb272fffd091">Follow-up tasks:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"ab8fa837-7656-4df5-9233-076ea56fa49b">
<li local-id=3D"14bd719b-98c2-4c5c-ba6e-c83a210ae9c8">
<p local-id=3D"ae9f0d5a0124"><strong>New Relic Dashboard Access: </strong>P=
rovide access to New Relic dashboards for the sales team and collect their =
feedback on dashboard usefulness. (David)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"be9a430d-7aae-450a-97c4-bf54bd98adf2">
<p local-id=3D"59e19b505dc5"><strong>Solace Environment Stability: </strong=
>Investigate with the test environment team and app owner to determine the =
root cause of Solace SIT and UAT environment instability and decide on appr=
opriate monitoring actions. (David, Jonan)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"aad1d856-aa6b-4947-963e-f35bee18f747">
<p local-id=3D"c8075b174eb1"><strong>Moogsoft and Ansible Integration: </st=
rong>Monitor progress and complete the integration of alerts to Moogsoft, f=
ollowed by Ansible script automation for service restarts, starting with ma=
nual execution if necessary. (Mary, Mark)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"94a0c559-dbff-46d2-8f78-fd2ce58f98f9">
<p local-id=3D"8deef3a3ea68"><strong>Firewall Approval for Enginium Monitor=
ing: </strong>Follow up with the observability team and Paula to obtain app=
roval for the pending firewall request required for Enginium non-production=
 environment URL monitoring. (Rae)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ef28d854-30ac-4943-8074-00545d992248">
<p local-id=3D"291e9cccc4a3"><strong>Firewall Rule Validation for Enginium:=
 </strong>Validate access to Enginium URLs after firewall changes and infor=
m Balaji upon confirmation. (Mark)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b495838f-b4da-4965-8753-de2c9b1c5360">
<p local-id=3D"0004cfcc211b"><strong>Runbook L2 Role Clarification: </stron=
g>Clarify and document the L2 roles and responsibilities in the Ingenium ru=
nbook, ensuring alignment with the current and future GOCC operating model,=
 and update the runbook for Japan market applications after September if ne=
eded. (Jonan, Balaji)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"51cfb783-1f0d-4793-a245-23c847f8722c">
<p local-id=3D"9a5f55f037be"><strong>Runbook Format Improvement: </strong>R=
eview and propose improvements for the format and versioning of application=
 runbooks to ensure they remain up-to-date and useful, considering automati=
on and metadata extraction options. (Jonan, Birger)</p></li>
</ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
------=_Part_112_101349099.1781767564401--
